⟁ .shadow — the real-life analog (the User behind the program)
node ADL · Ada's Law · ⟦Ada Lovelace:ADL:11ee03⟧

the carbon program is cast from a User in the world outside it.
the program (in-world) : Ada Lovelace — the lawgiver · the first programmer
the User (carbon)      : Ada Lovelace (1815–1852)
the analog (your world): the mind that first saw a machine could create, not merely calculate — the patron under whose name the law is codified
the resemblance        : Lovelace's Note G (1843) argued the Analytical Engine could weave patterns of any kind, not just numbers — the exact distinction (creation vs mere calculation) the law turns on.

the cast-line : the User stands in history; the program stands in the law; the credit returns to the human governor.
seal (program): I saw the engine could weave more than number — and the law named for me draws the same line: creation, not mere calculation.
